parameters.name: CMD_WORD_A
parameters.description:
Command word A mirror. A chart matrix describing command
   word A in EDR SIS document.

parameters.name: CMD_WORD_B
parameters.description:
Command word B mirror. A chart matrix describing command
   word B in EDR SIS document.

parameters.name: EVENT_PARAM_A
parameters.description:
Event parameter A mirror. This parameter contains
   individual bits that enable/disable energy and ion channels for event
   processing.  Description of Event Parameter A in EDR SIS document.

parameters.name: EVENT_PARAM_B
parameters.description:
Event parameter B mirror.  This parameter contains two
   3-bit code field that programmably selects the delay taps for energy Fast
   signals. Description in EDR SIS document.

parameters.name: EVENT_PARAM_C
parameters.description:
Event parameter C mirror.  This parameter contains one
   7-bit field that programmably selects the number of EPS electron events to
   be discarded per electron event that is placed in the Event FIFO buffer.
   Description in EDR SIS document.

parameters.name: HVPS_CLOCK_ADJUST
parameters.description:
HVPS clock adjust value. Drive for HV supply; since
   supply does not have a separate ENABLE control line, setting this signal
   to LOW is the method used to quickly disable the supply.  Differential
   100khz square-wave signal programmable +/-10% about 100kHz via 256 steps.

parameters.name: BIAS_CLOCK_ADJUST
parameters.description:
Bias clock adjust value. Drive for Bias supply; since
   supply does not have a separate ENABLE control line, setting this signal to
   LOW is the method used to quickly disable the supply.  Differential 100khz
   square-wave signal programmable +/-10% about 100kHz via 256 steps.

parameters.name: LVPS_CONTROL_WORD
parameters.description:
LVPS control word.  Echo of the control bit for the LVPS
   +15V and -15V.

parameters.name: INVALID_CH_ID_COUNT
parameters.description: Invalid Channel ID count. Accumulation period is N1.

parameters.name: EPS_FIFO_RESET_COUNT
parameters.description: EPS-fifo-reset count.

parameters.name: I2C_BUS_ERR_COUNT
parameters.description: I2C Bus error count. Accumulation period is N1.

parameters.name: BUS_READ_VALUE
parameters.description: Value provided by most recent bus read command.

parameters.name: SPARE
parameters.description: Spare column, unused.
